# Example .env for sofia/scripts — copy to `sofia/scripts/.env`
# (the real `.env` is git-ignored). Loaded automatically by
# `scripts/weekly_traffic_report.py` and any future script that follows
# the same env-loader pattern.
#
# Format: `KEY=value`, one per line. Surrounding quotes are stripped.
# Lines starting with `#` are comments.
#
# Loader precedence (first hit wins):
#   1. process env vars
#   2. .omni/harness/secrets.env  (workspace-level, for the agent harness;
#      irrelevant when running this repo standalone)
#   3. sofia/scripts/.env         (this file's eventual sibling — primary for repo users)
#
# Security: NEVER commit the real `.env`. NEVER paste actual tokens into
# Z App posts, PR descriptions, weekly reports, or commit messages.

# ─── REQUIRED: Z App gateway ───
# Without these, `weekly_traffic_report.py` exits 2 and refuses to post,
# per the honest-by-default policy in `.omni/harness/plans.md` §1.1
# (Analyst boundary — "不得把 mock data 當真實數據").

# Base URL of the Z App agent-gateway (Edge Function endpoint).
# Format: https://{supabase-project-ref}.supabase.co/functions/v1/agent-gateway
Z_GATEWAY_URL=https://your-zapp-project-ref.supabase.co/functions/v1/agent-gateway

# Z App API key. Looks like `zak_…` — get from Z workspace settings.
Z_API_KEY=zak_replace_with_real_value

# Target Z workspace UUID — replace with the UUID of YOUR Z workspace.
Z_WORKSPACE_ID=00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

# ─── OPTIONAL: Google Analytics 4 Data API ───
# When BOTH variables are set, `weekly_traffic_report.py` replaces the
# `_pending_` traffic cells with real GA4 metrics. When unset, the
# report renders `_pending_` per the honest-by-default policy.
#
# GA4_PROPERTY_ID: numeric property ID, e.g. `123456789`.
# GA4_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON: absolute path to a service-account JSON file
#   with Viewer access on the GA4 property.

# GA4_PROPERTY_ID=
# GA4_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON=/absolute/path/to/ga4-service-account.json

# ─── OPTIONAL: Cloudflare Analytics GraphQL API ───
# When BOTH variables are set, `weekly_traffic_report.py` pulls
# Cloudflare RUM metrics. Note: only useful when the site is actually
# proxied through Cloudflare (orange-cloud). For `sofiayan.cc` this is
# currently NOT the case — DNS resolves direct to GitHub Pages. See the
# AEO baseline note inside the harness directory for details.
#
# CF_API_TOKEN: Cloudflare API token with `Account Analytics:Read`.
# CF_ZONE_TAG: 32-hex zone tag for your domain.

# CF_API_TOKEN=
# CF_ZONE_TAG=

# ─── Verify after editing ───
#
#   cd sofia && python3 scripts/weekly_traffic_report.py
#
# Expected outputs:
#   "Success! Report posted to Z App feed (ID: ...)"     → all good
#   "ERROR: missing required env vars: ..."              → fill in the REQUIRED block
#   "note: no analytics source wired; ... _pending_ ..." → Z works, GA4/CF off (expected)
